identification.help: ?		Gets list of all available commands.ID?		Gets the product header and firmware version.RESTORE		Restores all settings to their default values.ECHO?		Gets echo status.ECHO=		Sets echo status, (0=Off, 1=On) When on all commands are echoed back.VLIMIT?		Gets output voltage limit switch setting (0=75V, 1=100V, 2=150V).INTENSITY?	Gets display intensity (0-15).INTENSITY=	Sets display intensity (0-15).XVOLTAGE?	Gets the output voltage for the x axis.XVOLTAGE=	Sets the output voltage for the x axis.XMIN?		Gets the minimum output voltage limit for the x axis.XMIN=		Sets the minimum output voltage limit for the x axis.SYSMIN?		Gets the minimum output voltage limit for the system.SYSMIN=		Sets the minimum output voltage limit for the system.XMAX?		Gets the maximum output voltage limit for the x axis.XMAX=		Sets the maximum output voltage limit for the x axis.SYSMAX?		Gets the maximum output voltage limit for the system.SYSMAX=		Sets the maximum output voltage limit for the system.DACSTEP?	Gets channel step size used with up/down arrow keys. (1-5000).DACSTEP=	Sets channel step size used with up/down arrow keys. (1-5000).Up Arrow	Increase selected channel by the set step size.Down Arrow	Decrease selected channel by the set step size.FRIENDLY?	Gets friendly name.FRIENDLY=	Set friendly name.SERIAL?		Gets serial number.CM?		Gets MDT694A compatibility mode (0=Off, 1=On).CM=		Sets MDT694A compatibility mode (0=Off, 1=On).ROTARYMODE?	Gets rotary mode. (0 = Default, 1 = 10 turn pot, 2 = fine)ROTARYMODE=	Sets rotary mode. (0 = Default, 1 = 10 turn pot, 2 = fine)PUSHDISABLE?	Gets push to adjust disabled. (0 = Enabled, 1 = Disabled)PUSHDISABLE=	Sets push to adjust disabled. (0 = Enabled, 1 = Disabled)>
